{
  "number": 823,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/823",
  "title": "beforeSearch hook",
  "body": "What about providing a `beforeSearch(helper)` hook that would be responsible one provided for launching the helper.search() method?\n\nIt would solve cases like:\n- I want to programmatically add filters based on the query: if the query changes, I want to update optional facet filters (cc @olance)\n- I want to avoid doing the first search query #4 \n- avoid search if chars.length < X #185 #182 \n- debounce the searchbox #776 #817 (only issue being you do not know it was triggered by the searchBox, but should be enough)\n- Let the developer choose to trigger the search (not sure fully resolved by this proposal) #769 \n\nThe naming might not be the best one, other possiblities:\n- searchHook\n- ??\n\n``` js\ninstantsearch(appID, apiKey, {\n  searchHook: function(helper) {\n    // once you define the search hook, it's your responsability to call helper.search, otherwise: no search is done\n  }\n})\n```\n",
